name: Logo Interpreter
description: A Logo interpreter from a website

commands.description: begins a new path, or resets the current path.  WebLogo's arc command is similar but WebLogo's arc command would show a different part of the arc. right 180 arc :angle :radius left 180 might be a good translation in WebLogo.
begins a new path, or resets the current path
deletes/cancels the current path
clears the graphics canvas.
clears the graphics canvas and moves the turtle at the initial position
Draws a cubic Bezier curve
tells the turtle that it can't move past the edges of the screen

fills a circle, with the turtle at the center, with the specified radius.  In WebLogo, the circle command is very similar except that WebLogo will stroke the circle too.  penUp circle :radius penDown might be a good translation in WebLogo.
fills the current path with the current filling color (default white)
fills a rectangle with the specified width and height and the turtle at the center
takes a word or list as input, and fills the input on the graphics canvas, starting at the turtle's position
the "flag" procedure draws a small national flag onto the canvas
draws a graphic object with the turtle at the center.  The most similar command in WebLogo would be image.
draws a graphic object with the turtle at the center. The turtle is not moving while drawing the object.  The most similar command in WebLogo would be imageAlpha.
sets the drawing mode to ERASE
(default) sets the drawing mode to PAINT
Draws a quadratic Bezier curve

draws a rectangle with the specified width and height and the turtle at the center.  WebLogo's rect command is the most similar command except that WebLogo's rect command doesn't take a rotation argument and just uses the turtle's current heading.
sets the background color of the canvas
sets a background image using the image name.  The most similar commands in WebLogo would be image and imageAlpha.
sets the blur level for shadows
sets the shadow color
the default position of the shadow is exactly under the shape (not visible)
Using this procedure you can stamp a copy of the turtle shape onto the canvas at the current turtle position.  The most similar command in WebLogo would be image.
strokes/draws the current path with the current line/stroke color (default black)
waits a number of milliseconds before executing the next command
tells the turtle that can move past the edges of the screen, unbounded
Tells the turtle to enter wrap mode
